2:
Who has urged this king to come from the east?
\q1 Who has commissioned this king to work for him? Whoever it is, he enabled his army to defeat many nations
\q2 and to trample their kings under his feet;
\q1 to cut their enemies into tiny pieces with their swords;
\q2 to make their enemies scatter with their bows, like the wind scatters chaff.
\q1

8:
Yahweh continues to say, "You people of Israel are my servants;
\q2 you are descendants of Jacob, whom I chose;
\q2 you are descendants of Abraham, who I said was my friend.
\q1
